item.title: What Gets The People Going?
item.description: An analysis of pedestrian activity in Melbourne Walking is universally lauded as the most efficient method of transportation of our human selves. Walking burns calories, engages our muscles and balance and encourages healthy mindsets through brain oxidation and the intake of fresh air. It’s fast and easily maintained – there’s no need to refuel, we can get out the door and be on our way immediately. Despite its ease of access however, pacing about is not always a comfortable experience.
